                                                            rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/simat/EngineeredMaterial> ;
                                                            rdfs:comment """In materials science, a sandwich-structured composite is a special class of composite materials that is fabricated by attaching two thin-but-stiff skins to a lightweight-but-thick core. The core material is normally of low strength, but its greater thickness provides the sandwich composite with high bending stiffness with overall low density. 
(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sandwich-structured_composite)"""@en ;
                                                            rdfs:label "Sandwich material"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/simat/SatinWeave
