                                                                      rdfs:comment """Semicrystalline polymers are defined as polymers that consist of both amorphous and crystalline regions, with crystallinity ranging from 10% to 80%. These polymers have ordered molecular structures and exhibit precise melting points, transitioning to a low viscous liquid upon heating rather than melting gradually.
(https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/engineering/semicrystalline-polymer)"""@en ;
                                                                      rdfs:label "Semi-cristalline thermoplast"@en .


