(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3D_scanning)"""@en ;
                                                                        rdfs:label "3D scanning"@en .


###  http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing
owl:Thing rdf:type owl:Class .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Activity
prov:Activity rdf:type owl:Class ;
              owl:disjointWith prov:Entity ;
              rdfs:comment "something that occurs over a period of time and acts upon or with entities. It may include consuming, processing, transforming, modifying, relocating, using, or generating entities"@en ;
              rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
              rdfs:label "Activity" ,
                         "Activity"@en ;
              prov:category "starting-point" ;
              prov:component "entities-activities" ;
              prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
              prov:definition "An activity is something that occurs over a period of time and acts upon or with entities; it may include consuming, processing, transforming, modifying, relocating, using, or generating entities." ;
              prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-Activity"^^xsd:anyURI ;
              prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Activity"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#ActivityInfluence
prov:ActivityInfluence rdf:type owl:Class ;
                       rdfs:subClassOf prov:Influence ,
                                       [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                         owl:onProperty prov:hadActivity ;
                                         owl:maxCardinality "0"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger
                                       ] ;
                       owl:disjointWith prov:EntityInfluence ;
                       rdfs:comment "ActivityInfluence provides additional descriptions of an Activity's binary influence upon any other kind of resource. Instances of ActivityInfluence use the prov:activity property to cite the influencing Activity."@en ,
                                    "It is not recommended that the type ActivityInfluence be asserted without also asserting one of its more specific subclasses."@en ;
                       rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                       rdfs:label "ActivityInfluence" ;
                       rdfs:seeAlso prov:activity ;
                       prov:category "qualified" ;
                       prov:editorsDefinition "ActivitiyInfluence is the capacity of an activity to have an effect on the character, development, or behavior of another by means of generation, invalidation, communication, or other."@en .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Agent
prov:Agent rdf:type owl:Class ;
           owl:disjointWith prov:InstantaneousEvent ;
           rdfs:comment "something that bears some form of responsibility for an activity taking place, for the existence of an entity, or for another agent's activity"@en ;
           rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
           rdfs:label "Agent" ,
                      "Agent"@en ;
           prov:category "starting-point" ;
           prov:component "agents-responsibility" ;
           prov:definition "An agent is something that bears some form of responsibility for an activity taking place, for the existence of an entity, or for another agent's activity. "@en ;
           prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-agent"^^xsd:anyURI ;
           prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Agent"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#AgentInfluence
prov:AgentInfluence rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf prov:Influence ;
                    rdfs:comment "AgentInfluence provides additional descriptions of an Agent's binary influence upon any other kind of resource. Instances of AgentInfluence use the prov:agent property to cite the influencing Agent."@en ,
                                 "It is not recommended that the type AgentInfluence be asserted without also asserting one of its more specific subclasses."@en ,
                                 "the capacity of an agent to have an effect on the character, development, or behavior of another by means of attribution, association, delegation, or other"@en ;
                    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                    rdfs:label "Agent influcence"@en ,
                               "AgentInfluence" ;
                    rdfs:seeAlso prov:agent ;
                    prov:category "qualified" ;
                    prov:editorsDefinition "AgentInfluence is the capacity of an agent to have an effect on the character, development, or behavior of another by means of attribution, association, delegation, or other."@en .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Association
prov:Association rdf:type owl:Class ;
                 rdfs:subClassOf prov:AgentInfluence ;
                 rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Association provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasAssociatedWith relation from an prov:Activity to some prov:Agent that had some responsiblity for it. For example, :baking prov:wasAssociatedWith :baker; prov:qualifiedAssociation [ a prov:Association; prov:agent :baker; :foo :bar ]."@en ,
                              "an assignment of responsibility to an agent for an activity, indicating that the agent had a role in the activity"@en ;
                 rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                 rdfs:label "Association" ,
                            "Association"@en ;
                 prov:category "qualified" ;
                 prov:component "agents-responsibility" ;
                 prov:definition "An activity association is an assignment of responsibility to an agent for an activity, indicating that the agent had a role in the activity. It further allows for a plan to be specified, which is the plan intended by the agent to achieve some goals in the context of this activity."@en ;
                 prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-Association"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                 prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Association"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                 prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasAssociatedWith .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution
prov:Attribution rdf:type owl:Class ;
                 rdfs:subClassOf prov:AgentInfluence ;
                 rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Attribution provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasAttributedTo relation from an prov:Entity to some prov:Agent that had some responsible for it. For example, :cake prov:wasAttributedTo :baker; prov:qualifiedAttribution [ a prov:Attribution; prov:entity :baker; :foo :bar ]."@en ,
                              "the ascribing of an entity to an agent"@en ;
                 rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                 rdfs:label "Attribution" ,
                            "Attribution"@en ;
                 prov:category "qualified" ;
                 prov:component "agents-responsibility" ;
                 prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                 prov:definition """Attribution is the ascribing of an entity to an agent.

When an entity e is attributed to agent ag, entity e was generated by some unspecified activity that in turn was associated to agent ag. Thus, this relation is useful when the activity is not known, or irrelevant."""@en ;
                 prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-attribution"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                 prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-attribution"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                 prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasAttributedTo .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Bundle
prov:Bundle rdf:type owl:Class ;
            rdfs:subClassOf prov:Entity ;
            rdfs:comment "Note that there are kinds of bundles (e.g. handwritten letters, audio recordings, etc.) that are not expressed in PROV-O, but can be still be described by PROV-O."@en ;
            rdfs:label "Bundle" ;
            prov:category "expanded" ;
            prov:definition "A bundle is a named set of provenance descriptions, and is itself an Entity, so allowing provenance of provenance to be expressed."@en ;
            prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-bundle-entity"^^xsd:anyURI ;
            prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-bundle-declaration"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Collection
prov:Collection rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf prov:Entity ;
                rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                rdfs:label "Collection" ;
                prov:category "expanded" ;
                prov:component "collections" ;
                prov:definition "A collection is an entity that provides a structure to some constituents, which are themselves entities. These constituents are said to be member of the collections."@en ;
                prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-collection"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Communication
prov:Communication rdf:type owl:Class ;
                   rdfs:subClassOf prov:ActivityInfluence ;
                   rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Communication provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasInformedBy relation from an informed prov:Activity to the prov:Activity that informed it. For example, :you_jumping_off_bridge prov:wasInformedBy :everyone_else_jumping_off_bridge; prov:qualifiedCommunication [ a prov:Communication; prov:activity :everyone_else_jumping_off_bridge; :foo :bar ]."@en ;
                   rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                   rdfs:label "Communication" ;
                   prov:category "qualified" ;
                   prov:component "entities-activities" ;
                   prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                   prov:definition "Communication is the exchange of an entity by two activities, one activity using the entity generated by the other." ;
                   prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-Communication"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                   prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-wasInformedBy"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                   prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasInformedBy .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Delegation
prov:Delegation rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf prov:AgentInfluence ;
                rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Delegation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:actedOnBehalfOf relation from a performing prov:Agent to some prov:Agent for whom it was performed. For example, :mixing prov:wasAssociatedWith :toddler . :toddler prov:actedOnBehalfOf :mother; prov:qualifiedDelegation [ a prov:Delegation; prov:entity :mother; :foo :bar ]."@en ;
                rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                rdfs:label "Delegation" ;
                prov:category "qualified" ;
                prov:component "agents-responsibility" ;
                prov:definition """Delegation is the assignment of authority and responsibility to an agent (by itself or by another agent) to carry out a specific activity as a delegate or representative, while the agent it acts on behalf of retains some responsibility for the outcome of the delegated work.

For example, a student acted on behalf of his supervisor, who acted on behalf of the department chair, who acted on behalf of the university; all those agents are responsible in some way for the activity that took place but we do not say explicitly who bears responsibility and to what degree."""@en ;
                prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-delegation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-delegation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                prov:unqualifiedForm prov:actedOnBehalfOf .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Derivation
prov:Derivation rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf prov:EntityInfluence ,
                                prov:Usage ;
                rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Derivation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasDerivedFrom relation from some derived prov:Entity to another prov:Entity from which it was derived. For example, :chewed_bubble_gum prov:wasDerivedFrom :unwrapped_bubble_gum; prov:qualifiedDerivation [ a prov:Derivation; prov:entity :unwrapped_bubble_gum; :foo :bar ]."@en ,
                             "The more specific forms of prov:Derivation (i.e., prov:Revision, prov:Quotation, prov:PrimarySource) should be asserted if they apply."@en ,
                             "a transformation of an entity into another, an update of an entity resulting in a new one, or the construction of a new entity based on a pre-existing entity"@en ;
                rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                rdfs:label "Derivation" ,
                           "Derivation"@en ;
                prov:category "qualified" ;
                prov:component "derivations" ;
                prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                prov:definition "A derivation is a transformation of an entity into another, an update of an entity resulting in a new one, or the construction of a new entity based on a pre-existing entity."@en ;
                prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-Derivation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#Derivation-Relation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasDerivedFrom .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#EmptyCollection
prov:EmptyCollection rdf:type owl:Class ;
                     rdfs:subClassOf prov:Collection .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#End
prov:End rdf:type owl:Class ;
         rdfs:subClassOf prov:EntityInfluence ,
                         prov:InstantaneousEvent ;
         rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:End provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasEndedBy relation from some ended prov:Activity to an prov:Entity that ended it. For example, :ball_game prov:wasEndedBy :buzzer; prov:qualifiedEnd [ a prov:End; prov:entity :buzzer; :foo :bar; prov:atTime '2012-03-09T08:05:08-05:00'^^xsd:dateTime ]."@en ;
         rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
         rdfs:label "End" ;
         prov:category "qualified" ;
         prov:component "entities-activities" ;
         prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
         prov:definition "End is when an activity is deemed to have been ended by an entity, known as trigger. The activity no longer exists after its end. Any usage, generation, or invalidation involving an activity precedes the activity's end. An end may refer to a trigger entity that terminated the activity, or to an activity, known as ender that generated the trigger."@en ;
         prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-End"^^xsd:anyURI ;
         prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-End"^^xsd:anyURI ;
         prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasEndedBy .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity
prov:Entity rdf:type owl:Class ;
            owl:disjointWith prov:InstantaneousEvent ;
            rdfs:comment """a physical, digital, conceptual, or other kind of thing with some fixed aspects
(http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity)"""@en ;
            rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
            rdfs:label "Entity" ,
                       "Entity"@en ;
            prov:category "starting-point" ;
            prov:component "entities-activities" ;
            prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
            prov:definition "An entity is a physical, digital, conceptual, or other kind of thing with some fixed aspects; entities may be real or imaginary. "@en ;
            prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-entity"^^xsd:anyURI ;
            prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Entity"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#EntityInfluence
prov:EntityInfluence rdf:type owl:Class ;
                     rdfs:subClassOf prov:Influence ;
                     rdfs:comment "EntityInfluence provides additional descriptions of an Entity's binary influence upon any other kind of resource. Instances of EntityInfluence use the prov:entity property to cite the influencing Entity."@en ,
                                  "It is not recommended that the type EntityInfluence be asserted without also asserting one of its more specific subclasses."@en ,
                                  "the capacity of an entity to have an effect on the character, development, or behavior of another by means of usage, start, end, derivation, or other"@en ;
                     rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                     rdfs:label "Entity influence"@en ,
                                "EntityInfluence" ;
                     rdfs:seeAlso prov:entity ;
                     prov:category "qualified" ;
                     prov:editorsDefinition "EntityInfluence is the capacity of an entity to have an effect on the character, development, or behavior of another by means of usage, start, end, derivation, or other. "@en .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Generation
prov:Generation rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf prov:ActivityInfluence ,
                                prov:InstantaneousEvent ;
                rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Generation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasGeneratedBy relation from a generated prov:Entity to the prov:Activity that generated it. For example, :cake prov:wasGeneratedBy :baking; prov:qualifiedGeneration [ a prov:Generation; prov:activity :baking; :foo :bar ]."@en ;
                rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                rdfs:label "Generation" ;
                prov:category "qualified" ;
                prov:component "entities-activities" ;
                prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                prov:definition "Generation is the completion of production of a new entity by an activity. This entity did not exist before generation and becomes available for usage after this generation."@en ;
                prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-Generation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Generation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasGeneratedBy .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Influence
prov:Influence rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Influence provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasInfluencedBy relation from some influenced Activity, Entity, or Agent to the influencing Activity, Entity, or Agent. For example, :stomach_ache prov:wasInfluencedBy :spoon; prov:qualifiedInfluence [ a prov:Influence; prov:entity :spoon; :foo :bar ] . Because prov:Influence is a broad relation, the more specific relations (Communication, Delegation, End, etc.) should be used when applicable."@en ,
                            "Because prov:Influence is a broad relation, its most specific subclasses (e.g. prov:Communication, prov:Delegation, prov:End, prov:Revision, etc.) should be used when applicable."@en ,
                            "the capacity of an entity, activity, or agent to have an effect on the character, development, or behavior of another by means of usage, start, end, generation, invalidation, communication, derivation, attribution, association, or delegation"@en ;
               rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
               rdfs:label "Influence" ,
                          "Influence"@en ;
               prov:category "qualified" ;
               prov:component "derivations" ;
               prov:definition "Influence is the capacity of an entity, activity, or agent to have an effect on the character, development, or behavior of another by means of usage, start, end, generation, invalidation, communication, derivation, attribution, association, or delegation."@en ;
               prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-influence"^^xsd:anyURI ;
               prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-influence"^^xsd:anyURI ;
               prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasInfluencedBy .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#InstantaneousEvent
prov:InstantaneousEvent rdf:type owl:Class ;
                        rdfs:comment "An instantaneous event, or event for short, happens in the world and marks a change in the world, in its activities and in its entities. The term 'event' is commonly used in process algebra with a similar meaning. Events represent communications or interactions; they are assumed to be atomic and instantaneous."@en ,
                                     "marks a transition in the world. Instantaneous events include generation, usage, or invalidation of entities, as well as starting or ending of activities"@en ;
                        rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                        rdfs:label "Instantaneous event"@en ,
                                   "InstantaneousEvent" ;
                        prov:category "qualified" ;
                        prov:component "entities-activities" ;
                        prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#dfn-event"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                        prov:definition "The PROV data model is implicitly based on a notion of instantaneous events (or just events), that mark transitions in the world. Events include generation, usage, or invalidation of entities, as well as starting or ending of activities. This notion of event is not first-class in the data model, but it is useful for explaining its other concepts and its semantics."@en .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Invalidation
prov:Invalidation rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf prov:ActivityInfluence ,
                                  prov:InstantaneousEvent ;
                  rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Invalidation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasInvalidatedBy relation from an invalidated prov:Entity to the prov:Activity that invalidated it. For example, :uncracked_egg prov:wasInvalidatedBy :baking; prov:qualifiedInvalidation [ a prov:Invalidation; prov:activity :baking; :foo :bar ]."@en ;
                  rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                  rdfs:label "Invalidation" ;
                  prov:category "qualified" ;
                  prov:component "entities-activities" ;
                  prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                  prov:definition "Invalidation is the start of the destruction, cessation, or expiry of an existing entity by an activity. The entity is no longer available for use (or further invalidation) after invalidation. Any generation or usage of an entity precedes its invalidation." ;
                  prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-Invalidation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                  prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Invalidation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                  prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasInvalidatedBy .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Location
prov:Location rdf:type owl:Class ;
              owl:equivalentClass <https://w3id.org/polymat/Location> ;
              rdfs:label "Location" ;
              rdfs:seeAlso prov:atLocation ;
              prov:category "expanded" ;
              prov:definition "A location can be an identifiable geographic place (ISO 19112), but it can also be a non-geographic place such as a directory, row, or column. As such, there are numerous ways in which location can be expressed, such as by a coordinate, address, landmark, and so forth."@en ;
              prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-attribute-location"^^xsd:anyURI ;
              prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-attribute"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Organization
prov:Organization rdf:type owl:Class ;
                  rdfs:subClassOf prov:Agent ;
                  rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                  rdfs:label "Organization" ;
                  prov:category "expanded" ;
                  prov:component "agents-responsibility" ;
                  prov:definition "An organization is a social or legal institution such as a company, society, etc." ;
                  prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-agent"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                  prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-types"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Person
prov:Person rdf:type owl:Class ;
            rdfs:subClassOf prov:Agent ;
            rdfs:comment "Person agents are people."@en ;
            rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
            rdfs:label "Person" ,
                       "Person"@en ;
            prov:category "expanded" ;
            prov:component "agents-responsibility" ;
            prov:definition "Person agents are people."@en ;
            prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-agent"^^xsd:anyURI ;
            prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-types"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Plan
prov:Plan rdf:type owl:Class ;
          rdfs:subClassOf prov:Entity ;
          rdfs:comment "There exist no prescriptive requirement on the nature of plans, their representation, the actions or steps they consist of, or their intended goals. Since plans may evolve over time, it may become necessary to track their provenance, so plans themselves are entities. Representing the plan explicitly in the provenance can be useful for various tasks: for example, to validate the execution as represented in the provenance record, to manage expectation failures, or to provide explanations."@en ;
          rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
          rdfs:label "Plan" ;
          prov:category "expanded" ,
                        "qualified" ;
          prov:component "agents-responsibility" ;
          prov:definition "A plan is an entity that represents a set of actions or steps intended by one or more agents to achieve some goals." ;
          prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-Association"^^xsd:anyURI ;
          prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Association"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#PrimarySource
prov:PrimarySource rdf:type owl:Class ;
                   rdfs:subClassOf prov:Derivation ;
                   rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:PrimarySource provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:hadPrimarySource relation from some secondary prov:Entity to an earlier, primary prov:Entity. For example, :blog prov:hadPrimarySource :newsArticle; prov:qualifiedPrimarySource [ a prov:PrimarySource; prov:entity :newsArticle; :foo :bar ] ."@en ;
                   rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                   rdfs:label "PrimarySource" ;
                   prov:category "qualified" ;
                   prov:component "derivations" ;
                   prov:definition """A primary source for a topic refers to something produced by some agent with direct experience and knowledge about the topic, at the time of the topic's study, without benefit from hindsight.

Because of the directness of primary sources, they 'speak for themselves' in ways that cannot be captured through the filter of secondary sources. As such, it is important for secondary sources to reference those primary sources from which they were derived, so that their reliability can be investigated.

A primary source relation is a particular case of derivation of secondary materials from their primary sources. It is recognized that the determination of primary sources can be up to interpretation, and should be done according to conventions accepted within the application's domain."""@en ;
                   prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-primary-source"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                   prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-original-source"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                   prov:unqualifiedForm prov:hadPrimarySource .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Quotation
prov:Quotation rdf:type owl:Class ;
               rdfs:subClassOf prov:Derivation ;
               rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Quotation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasQuotedFrom relation from some taken prov:Entity from an earlier, larger prov:Entity. For example, :here_is_looking_at_you_kid prov:wasQuotedFrom :casablanca_script; prov:qualifiedQuotation [ a prov:Quotation; prov:entity :casablanca_script; :foo :bar ]."@en ;
               rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
               rdfs:label "Quotation" ;
               prov:category "qualified" ;
               prov:component "derivations" ;
               prov:definition "A quotation is the repeat of (some or all of) an entity, such as text or image, by someone who may or may not be its original author. Quotation is a particular case of derivation."@en ;
               prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-quotation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
               prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-quotation"^^xsd:anyURI ;
               prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasQuotedFrom .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Revision
prov:Revision rdf:type owl:Class ;
              rdfs:subClassOf prov:Derivation ;
              rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Revision provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasRevisionOf relation from some newer prov:Entity to an earlier prov:Entity. For example, :draft_2 prov:wasRevisionOf :draft_1; prov:qualifiedRevision [ a prov:Revision; prov:entity :draft_1; :foo :bar ]."@en ;
              rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
              rdfs:label "Revision" ;
              prov:category "qualified" ;
              prov:component "derivations" ;
              prov:definition "A revision is a derivation for which the resulting entity is a revised version of some original. The implication here is that the resulting entity contains substantial content from the original. Revision is a particular case of derivation."@en ;
              prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-revision"^^xsd:anyURI ;
              prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Revision"^^xsd:anyURI ;
              prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasRevisionOf .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Role
prov:Role rdf:type owl:Class ;
          rdfs:comment "the function of an entity or agent with respect to an activity, in the context of a usage, generation, invalidation, association, start, and end"@en ;
          rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
          rdfs:label "Role" ,
                     "Role"@en ;
          rdfs:seeAlso prov:hadRole ;
          prov:category "qualified" ;
          prov:component "agents-responsibility" ;
          prov:definition "A role is the function of an entity or agent with respect to an activity, in the context of a usage, generation, invalidation, association, start, and end."@en ;
          prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-attribute-role"^^xsd:anyURI ;
          prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-attribute"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#SoftwareAgent
prov:SoftwareAgent rdf:type owl:Class ;
                   rdfs:subClassOf prov:Agent ;
                   rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
                   rdfs:label "SoftwareAgent" ;
                   prov:category "expanded" ;
                   prov:component "agents-responsibility" ;
                   prov:definition "A software agent is running software."@en ;
                   prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-agent"^^xsd:anyURI ;
                   prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-types"^^xsd:anyURI .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Start
prov:Start rdf:type owl:Class ;
           rdfs:subClassOf prov:EntityInfluence ,
                           prov:InstantaneousEvent ;
           rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Start provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasStartedBy relation from some started prov:Activity to an prov:Entity that started it. For example, :foot_race prov:wasStartedBy :bang; prov:qualifiedStart [ a prov:Start; prov:entity :bang; :foo :bar; prov:atTime '2012-03-09T08:05:08-05:00'^^xsd:dateTime ] ."@en ;
           rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
           rdfs:label "Start" ;
           prov:category "qualified" ;
           prov:component "entities-activities" ;
           prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
           prov:definition "Start is when an activity is deemed to have been started by an entity, known as trigger. The activity did not exist before its start. Any usage, generation, or invalidation involving an activity follows the activity's start. A start may refer to a trigger entity that set off the activity, or to an activity, known as starter, that generated the trigger."@en ;
           prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-Start"^^xsd:anyURI ;
           prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Start"^^xsd:anyURI ;
           prov:unqualifiedForm prov:wasStartedBy .


###  http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Usage
prov:Usage rdf:type owl:Class ;
           rdfs:subClassOf prov:EntityInfluence ,
                           prov:InstantaneousEvent ;
           rdfs:comment "An instance of prov:Usage provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:used relation from some prov:Activity to an prov:Entity that it used. For example, :keynote prov:used :podium; prov:qualifiedUsage [ a prov:Usage; prov:entity :podium; :foo :bar ]."@en ,
                        "the beginning of utilizing an entity by an activity"@en ;
           rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov-o#> ;
           rdfs:label "Usage" ,
                      "Usage"@en ;
           prov:category "qualified" ;
           prov:component "entities-activities" ;
           prov:constraints "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-constraints-20130430/#prov-dm-constraints-fig"^^xsd:anyURI ;
           prov:definition "Usage is the beginning of utilizing an entity by an activity. Before usage, the activity had not begun to utilize this entity and could not have been affected by the entity."@en ;
           prov:dm "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-dm-20130430/#term-Usage"^^xsd:anyURI ;
           prov:n "http://www.w3.org/TR/2013/REC-prov-n-20130430/#expression-Usage"^^xsd:anyURI ;
           prov:unqualifiedForm prov:used .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Analysis
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Analysis> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Method> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "An act of determining the physical properties or chemical composition of an object"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Analysis"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/AnnotatedData
<https://w3id.org/polymat/AnnotatedData> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> ;
                                         rdfs:comment "Experimental data with additional information or labels assigned to them"@en ;
                                         rdfs:label "Annotated data"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Apparatus
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Apparatus> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                     rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Device> ;
                                     rdfs:comment "A thing designed to carry out a particular task or activity during experiment (e.g. containing a chemical reaction, measuring liquids), not plugged into an electrical source, not a machine"@en ;
                                     rdfs:label "Apparatus"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Arithmetic
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Arithmetic> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Calculation> ;
                                      rdfs:comment "Calculations involving the traditional operations on numbers (addition, substraction, multiplication, division, exponentiation, extraction of roots)."@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Arithmetic"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Author
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Author> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Role> ;
                                  rdfs:comment "The originator or creator of a work"@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Author"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Building
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Building> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/PhysicalLocation> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "An enclosed construction with walls and roof"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Building"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Calculation
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Calculation> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000015 ;
                                       rdfs:comment "The process of finding an amount or number using mathematics."@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "Calculation"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Client
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Client> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Role> ;
                                  rdfs:comment "A person who receives or buys laboratory service"@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Client"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Coating
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Coating> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf :SamplePreparation ;
                                   rdfs:comment "Applying a covering to the surface of an object (usually referred to as the substrate)"@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Coating"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/ComputationalModel
<https://w3id.org/polymat/ComputationalModel> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                              rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Procedure> ;
                                              rdfs:comment "The use of computers to simulate and study a complex system or a procedure"@en ;
                                              rdfs:label "Computational model"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Computer
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Computer> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Device> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "An electronic device used to process information that can be stored in the form of numbers or a continuous signal"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Computer"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Creation
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Creation> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Method> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "An action of bringing something into existence"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Creation"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Data
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Data> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Object> ;
                                rdfs:comment "Information collected for use"@en ;
                                rdfs:label "Data"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/DataFormat
<https://w3id.org/polymat/DataFormat> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> ;
                                      rdfs:comment """The definition of the structure of data within a database or file system that gives the information its meaning
(https://c3.ai/glossary/features/data-format/)"""@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Data format"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/DataRepository
<https://w3id.org/polymat/DataRepository> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                          rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DigitalLocation> ;
                                          rdfs:comment "A space or location where data is stored"@en ;
                                          rdfs:label "Data repository"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType
<https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Feature> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "specific category of data"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Data type"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Device
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Device> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000040 ;
                                  rdfs:comment "A physical thing made to fulfill a specific purpose"@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Device"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/DigitalData
<https://w3id.org/polymat/DigitalData> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Data> ;
                                       rdfs:comment "Data that exist in digital environments, e.g. digital files"@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "Digital data"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/DigitalLocation
<https://w3id.org/polymat/DigitalLocation> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                           rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Location> ;
                                           rdfs:comment "An electronic location used for communication between computer systems"@en ;
                                           rdfs:label "Digital location"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Document
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Document> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> ,
                                                    <https://w3id.org/polymat/Object> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "Records providing information or evidence of a process, an event or a subject that serves as an authority or for reference"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Document"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/ELN
<https://w3id.org/polymat/ELN> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                               rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Software> ;
                               rdfs:comment "A computer software developed to replace paper laboratory notebooks to help document experiments"@en ;
                               rdfs:label "ELN"@en ,
                                          "Electronic Laboratory Notebook"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/ELNRecords
<https://w3id.org/polymat/ELNRecords> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Document> ;
                                      rdfs:comment "Digital and organised documentation of laboratory activities and data within an Electronic Laboratory Notebook (ELN) system"@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "ELN records"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Elastomer
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Elastomer> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                     rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Plastic> ;
                                     rdfs:comment """A polymer that displays rubber-like elasticity
(https://goldbook.iupac.org/terms/view/ET07547)"""@en ;
                                     rdfs:label "Elastomer"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Equipment
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Equipment> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                     rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Device> ;
                                     rdfs:comment "A set of instruments and other elements (e.g. tools) designed to perform a certain activity, powered by electricity, in a stand-alone setup"@en ;
                                     rdfs:label "Equipment"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Experiment
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Experiment> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000015 ;
                                      rdfs:comment "A process in which hypothesis is tested in a controllable environment or a collection of quantitative data that describes a property of an entity or event."@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Experiment"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/FOSSSoftware
<https://w3id.org/polymat/FOSSSoftware> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                        rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Software> ;
                                        rdfs:comment "A computer software considered both free software and open-source software"@en ;
                                        rdfs:label "FOSS software"@en ,
                                                   "Free and open-source software"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Feature
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Feature> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000020 ;
                                   rdfs:comment "A distinctive attribute or aspect of something,"@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Feature"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Fitting
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Fitting> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Calculation> ;
                                   rdfs:comment "A process of choosing value for parameters in a mathematical function to best describe a set of data."@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Fitting"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/GenericDevice
<https://w3id.org/polymat/GenericDevice> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Device> ;
                                         rdfs:comment "A concrete device identified by its function or type, without needing to specify a unique identifier or detailed characteristics (e.g., any thermometer used to measure temperature)"@en ;
                                         rdfs:label "Generic device"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/GeoLocation
<https://w3id.org/polymat/GeoLocation> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/PhysicalLocation> ;
                                       rdfs:comment "Geographic coordinates of something"@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "GeoLocation"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/ImageData
<https://w3id.org/polymat/ImageData> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                     rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> ;
                                     rdfs:comment "Data produced by scanning a surface with an optical or electronic device; visual information in the form of pictures, graphics or photographs"@en ;
                                     rdfs:label "Image data"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/InhouseSoftware
<https://w3id.org/polymat/InhouseSoftware> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                           rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Software> ;
                                           rdfs:comment "A computer software developed in-house with a given organisation by itself, often for internal use only"@en ;
                                           rdfs:label "Inhouse software"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Instrument
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Instrument> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Device> ;
                                      rdfs:comment "A device used to perform measurements or manipulate variables to monitor or control values of certain parameters, usually powered by electricity"@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Instrument"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Laboratory
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Laboratory> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/PhysicalLocation> ;
                                      rdfs:comment "A place (a bulding, part of a building or other place) equipped for doing experiments (e.g. chemistry laboratory) or scientific tests (e.g. computer laboratory)"@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Laboratory"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/LaboratoryNotebook
<https://w3id.org/polymat/LaboratoryNotebook> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                              rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Document> ;
                                              rdfs:comment "Complete records of laboratory research or experiment"@en ;
                                              rdfs:label "Laboratory Notebook"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Linux
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Linux> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                 rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/OperatingSystem> ;
                                 rdfs:comment """Family of Unix-like operating systems that use the Linux kernel and are open source
(https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q388)"""@en ;
                                 rdfs:label "Linux"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Location
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Location> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000004 ;
                                    rdfs:comment "A particular place where something happens or is situated (or exists)"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Location"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/MacOS
<https://w3id.org/polymat/MacOS> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                 rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/OperatingSystem> ;
                                 rdfs:comment """Operating system for Apple computers
(https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q14116)"""@en ;
                                 rdfs:label "Mac OS"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Maintainer
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Maintainer> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Role> ;
                                      rdfs:comment "A person who is trained to keep a given device in good condition or develop procedures to be performed using the device"@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Maintainer"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Measure
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Measure> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf om-2:Measure ;
                                   rdfs:comment "Combines a number to a unit of a result of an actual measurement of a given quantity"@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Measure"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/MechanicalTestingEquipment
<https://w3id.org/polymat/MechanicalTestingEquipment> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Equipment> ;
                                                      rdfs:comment "Equipment to measure mechanical properties of a sample"@en ;
                                                      rdfs:label "Mechanical testing equipment"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Metadata
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Metadata> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "Data that provides information about other data, e.g. describes characterististics or attributes of experimental data (such as the data source, units of measurements, data quality indicators)"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Metadata"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Method
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Method> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Procedure> ;
                                  rdfs:comment "A systematic procedure for accomplishing something (the-how)"@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Method"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Microscope
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Microscope> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Equipment> ;
                                      rdfs:comment """A piece of equipment which is used to generate an image of the surface of a specimen, whether by focusing reflected light onto where it can be collected or by scanning a given area of the surface
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHMO_0000953)"""@en ,
                                                   """An optical equipment that uses a combination of lenses to produce magnified images of very small objects
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C50069)"""@en ,
                                                   """Equipment which magnifies the view on objects under increased resolution
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0400169)"""@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Microscope"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/MicrosoftWindows
<https://w3id.org/polymat/MicrosoftWindows> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                            rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/OperatingSystem> ;
                                            rdfs:comment """Family of computer operating systems developed by Microsoft
(https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q1406)"""@en ;
                                            rdfs:label "Microsoft Windows"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Modelling
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Modelling> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                     rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Calculation> ;
                                     rdfs:comment "The activity of using mathematical models to predict certain values of parameters or make calculations."@en ;
                                     rdfs:label "Modelling"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/NominalMeasure
<https://w3id.org/polymat/NominalMeasure> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                          rdfs:subClassOf om-2:Measure ;
                                          rdfs:comment "Combines a number to a unit of a result of an nominal value (theoretical or designated value used as a reference point) of a given quantity"@en ;
                                          rdfs:label "Nominal measure"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/NumericData
<https://w3id.org/polymat/NumericData> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> ;
                                       rdfs:comment "Data consisting of numerical values representing measurements or quantities"@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "Numeric data"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Object
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Object> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000004 ;
                                  rdfs:comment "A thing to which a specific action is directed but not a person"@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Object"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/ObservedParameter
<https://w3id.org/polymat/ObservedParameter> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                             rdfs:comment "Actual measurement or manifestation of a parameter - as a variable of a laboratory process or its elements, reflecting its value or characteristic as recorded or noted during the laboratory process"@en ;
                                             rdfs:label "Observed parameter"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/OperatingSystem
<https://w3id.org/polymat/OperatingSystem> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                           rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Software> ;
                                           rdfs:comment "A software system that manages computer hardware and software resources and provides a platform for running applications"@en ;
                                           rdfs:label "Operating system"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/OpticalMicroscope
<https://w3id.org/polymat/OpticalMicroscope> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                             rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Microscope> ;
                                             rdfs:comment """A  type of microscope that commonly uses visible light and a system of lenses to generate magnified images of small objects or structures
(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Optical_microscope)"""@en ,
                                                          """A microscope (device to magnify small objects) in which objects are lit directly by white light.
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C28265)"""@en ,
                                                          """A piece of equipment, consisting of an eyepiece, an objective lens, object turret, stage, and light source, which collects electromagnetic radiation in the visible range
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHMO_0000947)"""@en ;
                                             rdfs:label "Optical microscope"@en ;
                                             skos:altLabel "Light microscope"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Person
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Person> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000004 ,
                                                  prov:Person ;
                                  rdfs:comment "An individual human being"@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Person"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/PersonalLocalHardDrive
<https://w3id.org/polymat/PersonalLocalHardDrive> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                  rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataRepository> ;
                                                  rdfs:comment "A physical storage device directly connected to a personal computer that is used to store/manage digital data"@en ;
                                                  rdfs:label "Personal local hard drive"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/PersonalServerDrive
<https://w3id.org/polymat/PersonalServerDrive> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataRepository> ;
                                               rdfs:comment "A storage device connected to a dedicated server that is used to host/manage digital data"@en ;
                                               rdfs:label "Personal server drive"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/PhysicalData
<https://w3id.org/polymat/PhysicalData> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                        rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Data> ;
                                        rdfs:comment "Data in the form of physical objects, e.g. paper files"@en ;
                                        rdfs:label "Physical data"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/PhysicalLocation
<https://w3id.org/polymat/PhysicalLocation> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                            rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Location> ;
                                            rdfs:comment "A physical structure (e.g. building) or space (e.g. room) or place (e.g. geographical location)"@en ;
                                            rdfs:label "Physical location"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Plastic
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Plastic> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Polymer> ;
                                   rdfs:comment """A synthetic or semi-synthetic material that use polymers as a main ingredient;  due to plasticity, it can be molded, extruded or pressed into solid objects of various shapes.
(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plastic)"""@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Plastic"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Polymer
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Polymer> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/simat/EngineeredMaterial> ;
                                   rdfs:comment "A material made of long, macromolecular chains of repeating molecular units"@en ,
                                                """A mixture, which is composed of macromolecules of different kinds and which may be differentiated by composition, length, degree of branching etc.
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_60027)"""@en ,
                                                """A molecule composed of a connected set of monomeric residues
(http://semanticscience.org/resource/SIO_000314)"""@en ,
                                                """A substance or material consisting of very large molecules, or macromolecules, composed of many repeating subunits
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PROCO_0000054)"""@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Polymer"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Procedure
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Procedure> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                     rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000003 ,
                                                     prov:Entity ;
                                     rdfs:comment "A set of activities that is the accepted way of doing something"@en ;
                                     rdfs:label "Procedure"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/ProcessedData
<https://w3id.org/polymat/ProcessedData> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> ;
                                         rdfs:comment "Data derived from raw data through various transformations, calculations, filtering or other operations"@en ;
                                         rdfs:label "Processed data"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Product
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Product> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Role> ;
                                   rdfs:comment "A substance that results from a chemical reaction"@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Product"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Protocol
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Protocol> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Document> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "An official or formal record of an experiment, procedure or process"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Protocol"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Publication
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Publication> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Document> ;
                                       rdfs:comment "A book (or a part of it), report or a similar format that is published"@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "Publication"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/RawDta
<https://w3id.org/polymat/RawDta> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> ;
                                  rdfs:comment "Original, unprocessed data collected directly from experiment"@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Raw data"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Recipe
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Recipe> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Document> ;
                                  rdfs:comment "A specification of ingredients, proportions and methods necessary to produce an expected product"@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Recipe"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Request
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Request> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Document> ;
                                   rdfs:comment "A document providing information about procedure (e.g. laboratory test) being requested for"@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Request"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Role
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Role> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000023 ,
                                                prov:Role ;
                                rdfs:comment "A purpose that something has or a function that something plays in a particular situation, under certain conditions, within a given process etc."@en ;
                                rdfs:label "Role"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Room
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Room> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/PhysicalLocation> ;
                                rdfs:comment "A portion of space inside of a building separated by walls or partitions from other parts"@en ;
                                rdfs:label "Room"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/RuntimeEnvironment
<https://w3id.org/polymat/RuntimeEnvironment> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                              rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Software> ;
                                              rdfs:comment "A piece of software that is designed to run other software"@en ;
                                              rdfs:label "Runtime environment"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Sample
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Sample> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Substance> ;
                                  rdfs:comment "A small subset or portion of an object used to represent the whole of it"@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Sample"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/SamplePreparation
<https://w3id.org/polymat/SamplePreparation> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                             rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Method> ;
                                             rdfs:comment "An action of creating a sample or getting it ready for some procedure"@en ;
                                             rdfs:label "Sample preparation"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/ScanningElectronMicroscope
<https://w3id.org/polymat/ScanningElectronMicroscope> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Microscope> ;
                                                      rdfs:comment """A piece of equipment which is used to produce an enlarged image of a specimen by scanning a finely focused (<10 nm diameter) electron beam with an acceleration voltage of 50–150 kV across the specimen under vacuum and measuring the interaction of the electrons with the specimen
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHMO_0000941)"""@en ,
                                                                   """An electron microscope that scans the surface of a sample with a beam of electrons and detects the interaction of the electrons with the atoms on the surface to produce a topographical image of the sample
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C78814)"""@en ;
                                                      rdfs:label "Scanning electron microscope"@en ;
                                                      skos:altLabel "SEM"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/SecureData
<https://w3id.org/polymat/SecureData> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/DataType> ;
                                      rdfs:comment "Data with sensitive or confidential content that needs to be protected from unauthorised access, loss, or alteration"@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Secure data"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Software
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Software> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf prov:Entity ,
                                                    <https://w3id.org/polymat/Object> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "A set of instructions, data or programs used by a computer"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Software"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Specimen
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Specimen> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                    rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Substance> ;
                                    rdfs:comment "An individual object taken for study or analysis, representing a class of objects"@en ;
                                    rdfs:label "Specimen"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Substance
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Substance> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                     rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000040 ;
                                     rdfs:comment "A physical material with particular properties"@en ;
                                     rdfs:label "Substance"@en ;
                                     skos:altLabel "Compound"@en ,
                                                   "Matter"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/TensileTest
<https://w3id.org/polymat/TensileTest> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf :MechanicalTest ;
                                       rdfs:comment """A standardized materials science and engineering method in which a solid sample is subjected to a controlled tension until failure; properties that are directly measured via a tensile test are ultimate tensile strength, breaking strength, maximum elongation, and reduction in area; from these measurements the following properties can also be determined: Young's modulus (modulus of elasticity), Poisson's ratio, yield strength, and strain-hardening characteristics
(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tensile_testing)"""@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "Tensile test"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/TensileTestMachine
<https://w3id.org/polymat/TensileTestMachine> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                              rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/MechanicalTestingEquipment> ;
                                              rdfs:comment """Equipment for carrying out standardized tensile tests on a solid sample to determine its mechanical properties
(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tensile_testing#Equipment)"""@en ;
                                              rdfs:label "Tensile test machine"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Thermometer
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Thermometer> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Instrument> ;
                                       rdfs:comment "An instrument that records and displays the temperature"@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "Thermometer"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Thermoplastic
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Thermoplastic> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Plastic> ;
                                         rdfs:comment """A plastic that can be deformed by heating in a certain temperature range (thermoplastic); this process is reversible and can be repeated as often as desired by cooling and reheating, as long as no thermal decomposition of the material occurs 
(https://thermoplasticcomposites.de/en/2023/01/23/the-world-of-plastics/)"""@en ;
                                         rdfs:label "Thermoplastic"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/Thermoset
<https://w3id.org/polymat/Thermoset> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                     rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Plastic> ;
                                     rdfs:comment """A plastic that retains its state and shape after curing, the process is irreversible due to cross-linked polymer chains
(https://thermoplasticcomposites.de/en/2023/01/23/the-world-of-plastics/)"""@en ;
                                     rdfs:label "Thermoset"@en ;
                                     skos:altLabel "Duromer"@en ,
                                                   "Duroplast"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/TransmissionElectronMicroscope
<https://w3id.org/polymat/TransmissionElectronMicroscope> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                          rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Microscope> ;
                                                          rdfs:comment """A piece of equipment which is used to produce an enlarged image of an electron transparent specimen using a finely focused (<10 nm diameter) electron beam with an acceleration voltage of 50–150 kV under vacuum; the energies and intensities of the transmitted electrons are measured
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHMO_0001099)"""@en ,
                                                                       """A type of microscope that uses magnetic lenses to transmit a beam of electrons through a thin sample; the electrons are then focused on a fluorescent screen or another detector to form an enlarged image
(https://www.photonics.com/EDU/transmission_electron_microscope_TEM/d7604)"""@en ,
                                                                       """An electron microscope that transmits a beam of electrons through a finely sliced section of a specimen and creates an image of the sample based on its effect on the phase of the electrons that pass through
(http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C78813)"""@en ;
                                                          rdfs:label "Transmission electron microscope"@en ;
                                                          skos:altLabel "TEM"@en .


###  https://w3id.org/polymat/User
<https://w3id.org/polymat/User> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                rdfs:subClassOf <https://w3id.org/polymat/Role> ;
                                rdfs:comment "A person who is trained to use a specific device"@en ;
                                rdfs:label "User"@en .


#################################################################
#    Individuals
#################################################################

###  http://purl.org/dc/terms/
terms: rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ;
       terms:modified "2012-06-14"^^xsd:date ;
       terms:publisher <http://purl.org/dc/aboutdcmi#DCMI> ;
       terms:title "DCMI Metadata Terms - other"@en .


###  http://purl.org/dc/terms/Agent
terms:Agent rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ;
            terms:issued "2008-01-14"^^xsd:date .


###  http://purl.org/dc/terms/AgentClass
terms:AgentClass rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ;
                 terms:issued "2008-01-14"^^xsd:date .


###  http://purl.org/dc/terms/BibliographicResource
terms:BibliographicResource rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ;
                            terms:issued "2008-01-14"^^xsd:date .


###  http://purl.org/dc/terms/Box
terms:Box rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual .


###  http://purl.org/dc/terms/DCMIType
terms:DCMIType rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ;
               terms:issued "2000-07-11"^^xsd:date ;
               rdfs:comment "The set of classes specified by the DCMI Type Vocabulary, used to categorize the nature or genre of the resource."@en ;
